          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="tabs-placement-prop">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/tabs/#tabs-placement-prop"}>
              Tab placement prop
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The
            <.custom_inline_code>placement</.custom_inline_code>
            attribute in the Mishka Chelekom Tabs component, when used in vertical orientation, allows you to align the tabs to different positions within the container. By default, it's set to <.custom_inline_code>start</.custom_inline_code>, aligning the tabs at the top. You can modify it to
            <.custom_inline_code>center</.custom_inline_code>
            to center the tabs or
            <.custom_inline_code>end</.custom_inline_code>
            to place them at the bottom. This gives you flexibility in organizing the vertical layout, making it easy to adapt the component to various design requirements.
          </.cp>

