              <:panel>
                <.cp>
                  The Profile tab allows you to view and edit your personal details. Keep your information up to date to ensure a seamless experience across the platform.
                </.cp>
              </:panel>
              <:panel>
                <.cp>
                  In the Tickets tab, you can manage all your active and past tickets. Whether you need assistance or just want to check your ticket history, this tab has all the relevant details.
                </.cp>
              </:panel>
              <:panel>
                <.cp>
                  The Settings tab gives you access to customizable options for your account. Here, you can adjust notifications, privacy settings, and other preferences to personalize your experience.
                </.cp>
              </:panel>
            </.tabs>
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="tabs-scrollable-prop">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/tabs/#tabs-scrollable-prop"}>
              Scrollable prop
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            <strong>Scrollable trigger list:</strong>
            pass
            <.custom_inline_code>scrollable</.custom_inline_code>
            to keep the trigger list on a single line/column and let it scroll instead of wrapping. For horizontal tabs the trigger row scrolls horizontally; for
            <.custom_inline_code>vertical</.custom_inline_code>
            tabs the trigger column scrolls vertically. Useful on mobile or when there are many tabs in a narrow / short container. The scrollbar itself is hidden — users scroll via touch / trackpad / wheel.
          </.cp>
          <.cp>
            <strong>Note — needs a bounded size:</strong>
            the scroll only engages when the tab list overflows its container, so the developer must constrain that size. For horizontal, give the parent a
            <.custom_inline_code>max-width</.custom_inline_code>
            (or use a narrow column); for vertical, set a fixed height on the
            <.custom_inline_code>&lt;.tabs&gt;</.custom_inline_code>
            element via
            <.custom_inline_code>class</.custom_inline_code>
            (e.g. <.custom_inline_code>class="h-56"</.custom_inline_code>) — without a height there is nothing to overflow against and the tabs render at their natural size.
          </.cp>
          <.cp>
            This wraps the trigger list in the
            <.custom_inline_code>scroll_area</.custom_inline_code>
            component, so make sure
            <.custom_inline_code>scroll_area</.custom_inline_code>
            is generated alongside
            <.custom_inline_code>tabs</.custom_inline_code>
            (it is listed as a required dependency).
          </.cp>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="tabs-tab-slot-icons">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/tabs/#tabs-tab-slot-icons"}>
              Tab slot icons props
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The <.custom_inline_code>icon</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>icon_class</.custom_inline_code>, and
            <.custom_inline_code>icon_position</.custom_inline_code>
            are key props of the
            <.custom_inline_code>tab</.custom_inline_code>
            slot in the Mishka Chelekom Tabs component, designed to enhance the visual appeal and functionality of each tab. The
            <.custom_inline_code>icon</.custom_inline_code>
            prop allows you to display an icon alongside the tab label, improving user recognition. With the
            <.custom_inline_code>icon_class</.custom_inline_code>
            prop, you can apply custom CSS classes to style the icon, giving you control over its appearance. Additionally, the
            <.custom_inline_code>icon_position</.custom_inline_code>
            prop lets you decide whether the icon appears on the left or right of the tab label, offering flexibility in layout design.
          </.cp>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="tabs-tab-slot-badge">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/tabs/#tabs-tab-slot-badge"}>
              Tab slot badge props
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The
            <.custom_inline_code>badge</.custom_inline_code>
            property for the
            <.custom_inline_code>tab</.custom_inline_code>
            slot is a versatile feature that enhances the visual representation of tabs by adding badges. This property is accompanied by several supporting attributes to customize the appearance and functionality of the badge. The
            <.custom_inline_code>badge_color</.custom_inline_code>
            attribute allows you to specify the color of the badge to match your design theme. The
            <.custom_inline_code>badge_position</.custom_inline_code>
            attribute controls where the badge is placed relative to the tab, ensuring flexibility in design layout. The
            <.custom_inline_code>badge_size</.custom_inline_code>
            attribute determines the size of the badge, allowing for variations such as small, medium, or large badges based on your requirements. Finally, the
            <.custom_inline_code>badge_variant</.custom_inline_code>
            attribute provides an option to define the variant of the badge, such as solid, outlined, or subtle styles, adding further customization options to suit different use cases.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper code_class="text-sm" elements_class="space-y-5" code={@code_15}>
            <.tabs id="tab-example-1000" padding="large" color="danger" variant="pills">
              <:tab>Profile</:tab>
              <:tab badge="8">Tickets</:tab>
              <:tab>Settings</:tab>
            </.tabs>
            <.tabs id="tab-example-1001" padding="large" color="misc" variant="pills">
              <:tab
                badge_color="danger"
                badge="9+"
                badge_variant="bordered"
                badge_size="size-6 text-[11px]"
              >
                Notification
              </:tab>
              <:tab>Messages</:tab>
              <:tab>Account</:tab>
            </.tabs>
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.custom_block color="warning" position="left" class="my-8" border="medium">
            Use class prop to add your custom classes to each item slot
          </.custom_block>

